<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-40-0441 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper reviews current computer applications in the prediction ofcoal quality. The authors show that the importance of computer basedtechniques in the coal industry is now recognised by citing examplesof such techniques commonly used. These include: computer-assisted, wire-linelog determinations, coal quality modelling and washability requirementsmodelling. Software packages such as GEOLOG, MINER2 and MINESTAR arealso discussed. 2 refs., 3 figs., 1 tab.</TEXT></DOC>